0 GeV, and that of \\rtF up to 1x10^8\nGeV. In case of the \\neu\\to\\gamma\\axi decay, the Peccei- Quinn symmetry\nbreaking scale F_a can be explored up to 5x10^11 GeV. The mass of the decaying\nparticle can be determined by using the correlation between the energy and the\narrival time of the decay product.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 17 Jun 1997 11:54:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 24 Jun 1997 12:16:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-10-30"}
